        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p>Benajmin Waller (1716-1786) was a respected and influential lawyer, civil servant,
                community leader, and land developer. Born in King William County, Virginia, Waller
                was a student at the College of William and Mary and later studied law using Sir
                John Randolph's law library. </p>
